Content:
One of the dumbass things all of those "code rankings" things do is that they only look at 1 branch of 1 repo.
jl777/komodo might have "only" had 520 commits *to the master branch* in the last year, but other branches get that many in a week/month. And other projects stage like that as well.
Imo, any team that has tens of thousands of commits to master per year is repoing wrong to begin with
